<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9110eb59-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8785"><num value="8785">§ 8785.</num><heading> Termination</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9110eb5a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8785/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The provisions of sections 8721, 8722, 8723, 8725, 8726, 8727, and 8771 of this title, subchapter I, and subchapter III shall terminate on the date that is 30 days after the date on which the President makes the certification described in <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s8551/a">section 8551(a) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9110eb5b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8785/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Omitted</heading><content />
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id9110eb5c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/112/158/tVI/s605">Pub. L. 112–158, title VI, § 605</ref>, <date date="2012-08-10">Aug. 10, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/1265">126 Stat. 1265</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id9110eb5d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id9110eb5e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id9110eb5f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section is comprised of <ref href="/us/pl/112/158/s605">section 605 of Pub. L. 112–158</ref>. Subsec. (b) of <ref href="/us/pl/112/158/s605">section 605 of Pub. L. 112–158</ref> amended <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s8551">section 8551 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
